<Content>Great hotel!! Just got back from a four day stay at the Hestia with a group of friends.Location was excellent. Five minutes from the bustling Leiseplein area (with trams to all other areas of Amsterdam) yet situated on a quiet street. There was very little noise during the night.Check-in was fast, easy and efficient. The rooms were very clean and quite spacious for Amsterdam, equipped with a TV, radio, hairdryer, safe etc. Beds were comfy and there was spare blankets provided. The stairs were a bit steep but there was a perfectly accessible lift so it was easy to get up and down.Breakfast was totally fine, what I expected for the very reasonable price, and the coffee was delicious! There was a lovely veradah to sit outside, and a house cat named Gregory.Rooms were cleaned every day to a good standard and fresh towels were provided. However, what made this stay so enjoyable was the combination of excellent facilities for the price, and excellent customer service. It is a very personal service at the Hestia. Whenever we needed help, for directions or advice, nothing was too much trouble for them. We were able to store our bags for as long as necessary on the last day as we had a late connection.The Hestia is just fab, would recommend to anyone! 
