<Content>I thought it was pretty good I stayed at the Hotel during the weekend 19/22 October travelling with my wife and another couple. We were very lucky to have room 15 which is large, spacious and includes a balcony overlooking the rear of the premises. The room was clean, simple without being over decorated and had a bath and shower.Our friends felt aggrieved as they had paid the same price but were stuck in an attic room with two single beds pushed together. Their room was cramped. I loved our room though the lighting was very dim. The hotel is ideally located and once we discovered how the tram system worked it was easy for us to travel from near the hotel right to the heart of the city. The staff were very friendly and spoke excellent English. Breakfast was different to the good old fried breakfast and there was plenty of it. The one thing that was strange about Amsterdam is the thin narrow stairs which are very steep (great for the calf muscles) The lift helps though as without it i wouldn't recommend it for young children or the the elderly. I am sure there are many finer hotels in Amsterdam but you get what you pay for and afterall this is a capital city. Would I stay there again? Absolutely ! 
