<Author>HappyHols2007
<Content>Fantastic quality, great location, breakfast  I just got back from a 4-night stay here with my Mum and we felt that we couldn't have chosen a nicer hotel. For the price (we paid 140 euros per night for a large triple room as all twins were booked), it was superb. The room was HUGE (and had a balcony too), the breakfast was lovely with plenty of choice (cheese, ham, cereal, muesli, yoghurt, fruit, boiled eggs and a variety of breads to toast), and the little breafast room was delightful, with french doors leading out to small, sunny garden, which was frequented each morning by 3 green paraqueets! The location was perfect too. In a quiet, exclusive-feeling road, but just 5 minutes walk from the Leidseplein (a hub for nightlife and bars), canal bus stop for tours, and practically next door to the Rijks Museum, Van Gogh Museum and Vondel Park. Tram stops from the Leidseplein also take you to Dam Square or Centraal Station in around 5 minutes. Perhaps not ideal for younger traveller who want to be within a short walking distance of the old centre (home to the red light district, shops, famous 'cafes', Dam Square, lots of restaurants etc...), but for us this was a bonus - the centre, although the oldest part, is not exactly the most 'desirable' or pretty part of the city. We felt we were much better off where we were and really if you wanted to, you probably could walk to Dam Square within 30-40 mins. At the end of the day, Amsterdam is pretty small, so if you don't mind walking a bit it doesn't really matter where you are!All in all, a fantastic stay that could not be faulted. 
